    <h2>What each one actually is</h2>

    <h3>Nexrial — CTMS for independent sites</h3>
    <p>
      Nexrial is a site-operations CTMS built for small independent research sites and
      small site networks running 5–25 concurrent studies. Core workflows: subject
      tracking, visit scheduling, regulatory binder, delegation log with PI e-signature,
      monitoring visit management (including findings and action items), protocol
      deviations, IRB submissions, SOPs with version gating, training log with expiry
      tracking, consent version tracking, and invoice management.
    </p>
    <p>
      Pricing is published: <strong>$299/month Core, $599/month Pro</strong>, plus a
      Founding Site Program — 50% off for life for the first 3–5 sites ($149 Core / $299 Pro).
      No quote required.
    </p>

    <h3>Clinical Conductor — CTMS for site networks and health systems</h3>
    <p>
      Clinical Conductor was originally built as a CTMS for research sites and site
      networks. Advarra acquired it and now positions it alongside OnCore (for academic
      medical centers) and additional modules including eReg (regulatory document
      management), eSource (data capture), CCText (Advarra's HIPAA-messaging
      add-on), and CCPay (subject reimbursements). The platform targets organizations
      that want financial oversight, patient recruitment, and research portfolio
      management under one vendor, including health systems like Ascension and Velocity
      Clinical Research.
    </p>
    <p>
      Clinical Conductor pricing is not publicly listed. Advarra directs all pricing
      inquiries to their sales team. Contact Advarra directly for current pricing.
      <!-- Source: advarra.com/solutions-for/clinical-trial-sites/clinical-conductor-ctms/ fetched 2026-04-23 -->
    </p>
