    <h2>When to pick which</h2>

    <h3>Pick Nexrial if…</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>You run a small independent research site (1–3 locations, sub-$700/month CTMS budget)</li>
      <li>You need a delegation log, regulatory binder, monitoring-visit workflow, and PI e-signatures without an enterprise contract</li>
      <li>You want pricing you can evaluate without a sales call</li>
      <li>Your studies are sponsor-supplied — you need site-operations coverage, not participant reimbursement infrastructure</li>
      <li>You want a vendor built specifically for small site compliance, not a scaled-down enterprise platform</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Pick Clinical Conductor if…</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>You run a multi-site network or health system research operation with centralized financial management needs</li>
      <li>You need Epic EHR integration, participant SMS, or debit-card reimbursements as native capabilities</li>
      <li>Your organization requires ISO 27001 and SOC 2 Type 2 certification from day one</li>
      <li>You want a single enterprise vendor (Advarra) covering CTMS, regulatory documents, and data capture</li>
      <li>Your CTMS budget allows for a quote-based engagement with a sales team</li>
    </ul>
