    <div class="doc-block">
    <h2>FAQ</h2>

    <h3>Does Clinical Conductor include eReg (regulatory document management)?</h3>
    <p>
      eReg is an Advarra product but is sold separately from Clinical Conductor CTMS.
      The two can be used together as part of the Advarra platform. Nexrial includes
      regulatory binder functionality (document versioning, document-level signatures,
      audit trail) natively — no separate product required for basic regulatory
      document management.
    </p>

    <h3>Does Nexrial implement 21 CFR Part 11 controls?</h3>
    <p>
      Nexrial is designed against the controls of 21 CFR Part 11 Subpart B (electronic
      records). Audit-log integrity is enforced by three independent database-level
      defenses: UPDATE, DELETE, and TRUNCATE are revoked at the database user level,
      meaning audit records cannot be altered even by application code. A validation
      package (VAL-PLAN, IQ/OQ/PQ, VAL-REPORT) with executed-run evidence is
      available under NDA. Part 11 is a design standard, not a certification — see
      <a href="https://nexrial.com/trust">nexrial.com/trust</a> for the current control posture.
    </p>

    <h3>Can Nexrial scale to a site network?</h3>
    <p>
      Nexrial today is purpose-built for independent sites and small networks. Multi-site
      org hierarchy, cross-site reporting, and sponsor/CRO read-only portals are on the
      roadmap; pricing for a network tier has not been published. For large networks
      (10+ sites) where Epic integration and enterprise vendor SLAs are hard requirements
      now, Clinical Conductor's Advarra backing is worth evaluating in parallel.
    </p>

    <h3>Who owns Clinical Conductor now?</h3>
    <p>
      Clinical Conductor is owned and operated by Advarra, which also owns OnCore CTMS
      (academic medical centers), eReg, and eSource. Advarra serves approximately 3,500
      institutions and 50,000 investigators. Clinical Conductor continues to operate as
      a distinct product within that portfolio.
    </p>
